title: More: Tootie's January 2016 Mix
description:
A new year, more Tootie mixes. This mix was heavily inspired by Rock Band. It includes many artists and bands never before heard in a Tootie mix.

  Jessie J featuring B.o.B - Price Tag
  The Doobie Brothers - Long Train Runnin'
  The Bangles - Walk Like an Egyptian
  The B-52's - Rock Lobster
  Kenny Loggins - Footloose
  Men Without Hats - The Safety Dance
  Ke$ha - Blow
  R3hab - Hakuna Matata (Hardwell Edit)
  KSHMR & Marnik - Bazaar
  Leandro da Silva - Sing It Back
  Jewelz & Sparks - I Can Fly
  A-Trak & Milo & Otis featuring Rich Kidz - Out the Speakers
  KuPeR - Metrology
  Firebeatz & Jay Hardway - Home
  Sugar Hill & Nytron - Oooh
  Duran Duran - Hungry Like the Wolf
  Foreigner - Double Vision
  John Mellencamp - Hurts So Good
  Grand Funk Railroad - We're an American Band
  Janet Jackson - Black Cat
  Joan Jett & the Blackhearts - I Love Rock 'n Roll
  Kiss - Rock and Roll All Nite
  Jimmy Eat World - The Middle
  Hoobastank - Crawling in the Dark
  The Veer Union - Seasons
  Audioslave - Show Me How to Live
  Linkin Park - What I've Done
  Radiohead - Creep
  Down June - More

All tracks are sourced from lossless material. All of the compilations' songs utilize playback gain values from Tootie's personal volume-leveling procedure, resulting in a consistent overall listening experience without the need to adjust the volume between songs. The method focuses on vocal volume.
